User API – Postman Usage Guide
Base URL
http://localhost:3000/users

1. Create User (POST)

Method: POST
URL:

http://localhost:3000/users


Body (raw → JSON):

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "roles": ["PERSONAL"],
  "groups": ["GROUP_1"]
}

2. Read All Users (GET)

Method: GET
URL:

http://localhost:3000/users


No body needed.

3. Read User by ID (GET)

Method: GET
URL (example):

http://localhost:3000/users/2


No body needed.

4. Update User (PATCH)

Use when you want to update only specific fields.

Method: PATCH
URL (example):

http://localhost:3000/users/2

Example to update groups:
{
  "groups": ["GROUP_2"]
}

Example to update roles:
{
  "roles": ["ADMIN"]
}

Example to update name:
{
  "name": "New Name"
}

5. Delete User (DELETE)

Method: DELETE
URL (example):

http://localhost:3000/users/2


No body needed.
